videos.description: Manny Suarez draws two defenders and dishes it to Martin Krampelj for the easy dunk.
videos.headline: Creighton's ball movement leads to Krampelj dunk

videos.description: Khyri Thomas sprints to grab the offensive rebound and lays it in for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Creighton's Thomas shows hustle to get and-1

videos.description: Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. grabs his own miss, takes the hit and makes the layup for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Baylor's Lual-Acuil's determination on the offensive glass leads to and-1

videos.description: Khyri Thomas grabs the steal, misses the layup and Marcus Foster cleans up the miss for a two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Creighton turns defense into offense

videos.description: Davion Mintz throws a lob to Martin Krampelj in transition who finishes with a layup.
videos.headline: Krampelj lays in an alley-oop

videos.description: Mitchell Ballock swats a Baylor shot and dishes it to Ty-Shon Alexander who makes a tough layup over a defender.
videos.headline: Ballock's block leads to Creighton layup

videos.description: Ty-Shon Alexander throws a dime to Martin Krampelj who takes the contact and makes the layup for the and-1 bucket.
videos.headline: Krampelj completes reverse layup after foul

videos.description: King McClure drives baseline and attacks the rim for a 3-point play and a chance to tie the game at 50.
videos.headline: Baylor's McClure hits tough layup

videos.description: Baylor's head coach Scott Drew says his team took care of the ball and "took more high-percentage shots" in a 65-59 win over Creighton.
videos.headline: Drew: Baylor 'settled down' in second half
